Subject: Re: [T2] Please advise on a weird hot starting problem

E. Marc Coe wrote:
  >   I've got an 81 Vanagon, automatic.
>   She starts right up, even after sitting for a week.
>   But when I stop at a store and come back a few minutes later, she doesn't want to start back up.
> h, she cranks real good - the starter is fine, but she won't catch.  Only way I can get her
>   to start is to floor the accelerator and crank it for thirty or forty seconds straight.  She starts....so far.
>   When she is running she runs great.  Idles and accelerates beautifully.   
>   I thought it might be the fuel filter and switched that, but it didn't help.
>   Weird, huh?  Sitting for a week and everything is fine, but two minutes and no go!
>   I would greatly appreciate any help you can give.

Take a look at the Temp sensor II. Measure the resistance on this sensor 
at engine running temp and cold. Bentley has the specs in it. This could 
be the problem.

